#import "../../knot-typst-package/lib.typ": *
#show: codly-init

= Test Phase 4: Plot Support

This document tests the new plot support in Knot Phase 4.

== Simple ggplot2 Scatter Plot

Let's create a simple scatter plot:

```{r plot1}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
library(ggplot2)

gg <- ggplot(iris, aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width, color = Species)) +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Iris Sepal Dimensions")

typst(gg)
```

== Plot with Custom Size

Here we specify custom dimensions:

```{r plot2}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
gg2 <- ggplot(mtcars, aes(x = wt, y = mpg, color = factor(cyl))) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  theme_light() +
  labs(title = "MPG vs Weight", x = "Weight", y = "MPG", color = "Cylinders")

typst(gg2, width = 8, height = 5)
```

== DataFrame + Plot Combined

This chunk outputs both a table and a plot:

```{r combined}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
# Summary table
summary_df <- data.frame(
  Stat = c("Mean Length", "Mean Width", "N"),
  Value = c(mean(iris$Sepal.Length), mean(iris$Sepal.Width), nrow(iris))
)
typst(summary_df)

# Distribution plot
gg3 <- ggplot(iris, aes(x = Sepal.Length, fill = Species)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 15, alpha = 0.6, position = "identity") +
  theme_minimal()

typst(gg3)
```

== Done

All plots rendered successfully!
